        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-06-28T19:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-06-28T19:56:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <head>47. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Burma</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d47fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 411.90B41/5–856. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-06-28T20:56:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1956—8:56 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1305. Joint State–<gloss target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss> message. <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1138.<note n="2" xml:id="d47fn2">
                        <ref target="#d39">Document 39</ref>.</note> Battle Act directly controls
                    activities of US Government only not other governments. After complete review,
                    determination reached Burma eligible US assistance.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> Following considerations taken into account
                    in review: 1) for foreign policy reasons, assisting Burma urgent priority; 2)
                    because of declared neutrality <gloss target="#t_GUB1">GUB</gloss> will not give
                    assurances in manner and form originally requested by US (<gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 989, <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 1246s);<note n="3" xml:id="d47fn3">
                        <ref target="#d31">Documents 31</ref> and <ref target="#d38"
                        >38</ref>.</note>) assurances regarding rubber not vital because licensed
                    exports to <gloss target="#t_CPR1">CPR</gloss> only 5,000 tons and Burma’s
                    estimated export potential only ten-twelve thousand tons annually which would
                    not greatly change bloc capabilities if all shipped <gloss target="#t_CPR1"
                        >CPR</gloss> which not probable; 4) Cabinet officer (<persName
                        corresp="#p_KNU1">Kyaw Nyein</persName>) has stated to Embassy <gloss
                        target="#t_GUB1">GUB</gloss> not contemplating shipping strategic minerals
                    to bloc; 5) no other known potential Battle Act items available in Burma for
                    shipment to bloc or mentioned in Burma’s trade agreements with bloc; 6) <gloss
                        target="#t_GUB1">GUB</gloss> has licensing controls over strategic goods
                    including rubber which meet objectives Section 202 Battle Act; 7) Burma
                    currently cooperating with US to extent required by Section 203 of Battle Act
                    including supply adequate reports; 8) Burma advised that provision of Battle Act
                    will require (a) <pb facs="0104" n="76" xml:id="pg_76"/> termination of US
                    assistance if any Title I, Category A items are shipped to Communist bloc, or
                    (b) a determination of the President regarding the continuation of assistance if
                    Title I, Category B goods are shipped to bloc. (Information in final point
                    conveyed Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_WU1">Win</persName> May 11 and 12.
                        <persName corresp="#p_NU1">U Nu</persName> letter to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> May 22<note n="4" xml:id="d47fn4"
                        >See <ref target="#d40">Document 40</ref>.</note> shows <gloss
                        target="#t_GUB1">GUB</gloss> cognizant these Battle Act requirements.) End
                        <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Action cables follow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
